This paper deals with the problem of task planning for robots, specifically in predicting multiple task-level outcomes in a given environment. This falls under the category of robotics (cs.RO). The paper proposes a method that involves learning a neural net to encode likely outcomes from high level actions, which involves machine learning (cs.AI) and deep learning (cs.LG). The approach also generates image and pose predictions, which involves computer vision (cs.CV). Finally, the paper deals with the problem of navigating in a cluttered environment, which involves control systems (cs.SY).
